System.out.println(students.size()); // 2
System.out.println(students); // This will print student1 and student3 (because student2 is a duplicate)
```

#### 2. Use stream with distinct() and override equals().

```Java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student[] studentsArray = {
                new Student(1, &quot;Elon&quot;),
                new Student(1, &quot;Elon&quot;),
                new Student(2, &quot;Elon&quot;)
        };

        Student[] distinctStudents = Arrays
                .stream(studentsArray)
                .distinct() //uses equals()
                .toArray(Student[]::new);

        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(distinctStudents));
    }
}
```

